<p class="">establishment of the economic future of this country. When this conference has taken place I feel certain that, with the other developments to which I have referred, we can put our long-term affairs on a solid basis.<p></p> I would say to hon. and right hon. Gentlemen opposite, who seem to mock a great many of these developments and who seem to have taken very lightly some of the serious remarks that I have made today, that they do not seem to have accepted the problems of our country in the spirit that they should, which is that if we fail we fail together, and if we succeed we succeed together.</p>                    <div class="hidden-md hidden-lg" style="padding-left: 0px;">
